        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Are we actually open to taking on new members? Well, I'd assume we are considering I'm in. But do we actually go out and try to recruit untagged players? I know there's a bad rap on ninjaing (have no idea how that term came about) players from other guilds, but there are a lot of unguilded players out there.</P><P>If I was playing with some untagged people, do I have the right to tell them they should apply to Akalabeth? Or would I have to tell a full member that I found someone they should ask and that full member does the work? I really don't know. </P><P>What I do know, however, is that I'm sure there are lots of people out there who would love to be a member of a guild, but maybe have no idea of how to get into one, or why even. Heck, if Azzameen and Aidem never got Voltan and me into LOA, we'd probably have no idea of the wonderfull and enriched lives a guilded member leads.</P><P>So, can someone fill me in here?</P><P><img src="http://www.allizdog.com/daoc/waplespunk/images/Waplespunk_Logo.jpg" border=0><BR>Waplespunk the Yellow - Grillmaster of Stenchy's Traveling Circus<BR>Bruti - Stirfriar in Stenchy's Traveling Circus</P><P><BR>Edited by - Joxer_LOA on 05/13/2002  08:45:25</font></td>

