        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> If you find someone that is fun to be around, mature, good-natured... they can be invited into "Akalabeth" as a guest. It gives them, and us, a chance to get to know each other better. If they like what they see and want to join LOA overall, they are welcome to apply. The application questions and process is posted on this forum (and locked). </P><P>I am all about expanding Akalabeth with good people. It is a win-win situation.</P><P>Thanks for this question, Waple. I appreciate your effort to recruit new members... very cool.</P><P>Brym / Brimstone<BR>Co-GM, Akalabeth</P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
